        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13006",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\n\n$phpunit Zend_DateTest\nContent-type: text\/html\n\nPHPUnit 3.0.0 by Sebastian Bergmann.\n\n.FF.................F....................\n...................................I\n\nTime: 00:11\n\nThere were 3 failures:\n\n1) testCreationDefaultFormat(Zend_DateTest)\nFailed asserting that <string:2006-01-01T00:00:00+05:00> is identical to <string:2005-11-30T00:00:00+05:00>.\n\/cygdrive\/c\/gavin\/home\/src\/zftmp\/tests\/Zend\/DateTest.php:73\n\/usr\/local\/bin\/phpunit:40\n\n2) testCreationDefaultFormatConsistency(Zend_DateTest)\nFailed asserting that <string:2005-11-30T01:00:00-05:00> is identical to <string:2006-01-01T01:00:00-05:00>.\n\/cygdrive\/c\/gavin\/home\/src\/zftmp\/tests\/Zend\/DateTest.php:101\n\/usr\/local\/bin\/phpunit:40\n\n3) testGet(Zend_DateTest)\nexception expected\n\/cygdrive\/c\/gavin\/home\/src\/zftmp\/tests\/Zend\/DateTest.php:1022\n\/usr\/local\/bin\/phpunit:40\n\nFAILURES!\nTests: 77, Failures: 3, Incomplete: 1.\n\n$ svn update\nAt revision 3649.\n\n$ php -v\nPHP 5.2.1 (cgi-fcgi) (built: Feb 22 2007 13:57:31)\nCopyright (c) 1997-2007 The PHP Group\nZend Engine v2.2.0, Copyright (c) 1998-2007 Zend Technologies\n\n$ uname -a\nCYGWIN_NT-5.1 1.5.24(0.156\/4\/2) 2007-01-31 10:57 i686 Cygwin\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-26T16:55:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-26T16:55:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13013",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "See SVN 3662.\n\nget() now supports Zend_Date constants and php and iso format strings.\nIf no constant is given, toString() is called instead of processing it further within get().\n\nThis way the problem mentioned above does not exist anymore.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-27T02:58:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-27T02:58:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13052",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If toString() works, why add the formatting features of toString() to get()?\n\nWhy would developers ever use toString(), if get() does everything toString() does and more?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-28T15:08:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-28T15:08:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13055",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A user will probably use get() to get some return values from the actual date object.\n\nA user would probably use toString() when he want to have string output of the date object.\nAlso toString() is called automatically by php... __toString();\n\nget() is also used by object creation, because the original approach was to use the constants...\nThen you proposed also to have single strings parsed by object creation... so get() was extended to support\niso strings additionaly to constants... and then you said other strings should also be supported... now all possible ways are recognised by get(). And now you say this is not good ???\n\nIn my opinion it's good to have the functionallity seperated... toString() returns formatted strings only... get() calculates constants only... but on failure the function degrades to toString() and tries to generate the proper output.\n\nI see no negative or problems on this approach.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-28T15:41:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-28T15:41:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13057",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I never proposed extending get, just making \"new Zend_Date()\" work with format specifiers.\n\nThe negative comes from having two ways to do the same thing.  On other issues, the devteam often prefers to try and provide \"one way\" to do each task, without losing flexibility for users to change things.  One of the reasons given for the \"one way\" preference is to help avoid confusion among developers regarding which way to use under what circumstances.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-28T16:27:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-28T16:27:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13061",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Well.... we have the standard toString function which should be implemented because this is the standard way of getting output from an object.\n\nAnd we have the complete tree of get() functions. getDate(), getTime(), getHour() and so on...\nwhich are just a simplification for the default get() to simplify the useage of get().\n\nWhen we delete get() we would corrupt the API and have to rename all getxxx functions to toxxx functions... which does not describe exact what they are doing.\n\nIf we delete the toString() function we have other problems... one is the objects standard toString() function... the second is that toString does exactly what it should... it converts an date object TO-STRING().\n\nI see no problems in having both functions implemented and to auto-correct false input from the user for the get() function.\n\nBtw:\ntoString() can not work with the constants... this only works with the get() function. So this functions are not doing the same... get() is just failsave for userinput.\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-01T01:01:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-01T01:01:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13116",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As discussed in the community server, this issue is no longer a problem as with SVN 3697.\n\nAll related unit tests work.\nIf we find any problems we can reopen this issue anytime.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-03T03:47:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-03T03:47:23.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
